# Linux Commands Cheat Sheet

This is a collection of essential Linux commands, categorized for easy reference.

## 1. File and Directory Management
| Command               | Description                                        |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `ls`                  | List directory contents                            |
| `cd`                  | Change the current directory                       |
| `pwd`                 | Show current directory path                        |
| `mkdir`               | Create a new directory                             |
| `rmdir`               | Remove an empty directory                          |
| `rm -r`               | Remove directory and its contents                  |
| `cp`                  | Copy files or directories                          |
| `mv`                  | Move or rename files or directories                |
| `touch`               | Create a new empty file                            |
| `cat`                 | Display contents of a file                         |
| `ln -s`               | Create a symbolic link                             |

## 2. File Permissions and Ownership
| Command               | Description                                        |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `chmod`               | Change file permissions                            |
| `chown`               | Change file owner                                  |
| `chgrp`               | Change group ownership                             |
| `umask`               | Set default file permissions                       |

## 3. File Viewing and Editing
| Command               | Description                                        |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `cat`                 | View file contents                                 |
| `less`                | View file content interactively                    |
| `head`                | Show the first 10 lines of a file                  |
| `tail`                | Show the last 10 lines of a file                   |
| `nano`                | Open file in nano text editor                      |
| `vi` or `vim`         | Open file in Vim text editor                       |

## 4. Searching and Sorting
| Command               | Description                                        |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `grep`                | Search for a pattern in files                      |
| `find`                | Find files and directories                        |
| `locate`              | Find files by name                                 |
| `sort`                | Sort lines of text in a file                       |
| `uniq`                | Remove duplicate lines in a file                   |
| `wc`                  | Count words, lines, and characters in a file       |

## 5. Disk Usage and Management
| Command               | Description                                        |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `df`                  | Show disk space usage                              |
| `du`                  | Estimate file and directory space usage            |
| `mount`               | Mount a filesystem                                 |
| `umount`              | Unmount a filesystem                               |
| `fdisk`               | Disk partitioning utility                          |

## 6. System Information and Monitoring
| Command               | Description                                        |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `uname -a`            | Show system information                            |
| `top`                 | Show real-time process monitoring                  |
| `htop`                | Interactive process viewer                         |
| `uptime`              | Show how long the system has been running          |
| `free -h`             | Show memory usage                                  |
| `df -h`               | Show disk usage in human-readable format           |
| `lscpu`               | Display CPU architecture information               |
| `lsblk`               | List information about block devices               |

## 7. Process Management
| Command               | Description                                        |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `ps`                  | Show running processes                             |
| `top`                 | Display real-time processes and system resource usage|
| `kill`                | Terminate a process by PID                         |
| `killall`             | Terminate processes by name                        |
| `bg`                  | Resume a suspended job in the background           |
| `fg`                  | Bring a background job to the foreground           |

## 8. Networking Commands
| Command               | Description                                        |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `ping`                | Send ICMP echo requests to test network connectivity|
| `ifconfig`            | Configure network interfaces (deprecated, use `ip`)|
| `ip`                  | Show/manipulate network interfaces                 |
| `netstat`             | Show network connections and routing tables        |
| `curl`                | Transfer data to or from a server                  |
| `wget`                | Download files from the web                        |
| `ssh`                 | Securely connect to a remote machine               |

## 9. Archiving and Compression
| Command               | Description                                        |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `tar -cvf`            | Create a tarball archive                           |
| `tar -xvf`            | Extract a tarball archive                          |
| `gzip`                | Compress files with gzip                           |
| `gunzip`              | Decompress `.gz` files                             |
| `zip`                 | Compress files into a `.zip` archive               |
| `unzip`               | Extract files from a `.zip` archive                |

## 10. Package Management (Debian/Ubuntu)
| Command               | Description                                        |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `apt update`          | Update the list of available packages              |
| `apt upgrade`         | Upgrade all installed packages                     |
| `apt install`         | Install a package                                  |
| `apt remove`          | Remove a package                                   |

## 11. Package Management (Red Hat/CentOS)
| Command               | Description                                        |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `yum update`          | Update the list of available packages              |
| `yum install`         | Install a package                                  |
| `yum remove`          | Remove a package                                   |

## 12. User and Group Management
| Command               | Description                                        |
|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `useradd`             | Create a new user                                  |
| `usermod`             | Modify user account settings                       |
| `userdel`             | Delete a user                                      |
| `passwd`              | Change a userâ€™s password                           |
| `groupadd`            | Add a new group                                    |
| `groupdel`            | Delete a group                                     |

---
